{"questionId":"f196343a-4470-4649-8efb-edf349dd4393_22","correctAnswer":"D","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Use the factored form","content":"Since the parabola has roots $8$ and $-5$, $f(x)=a(x-8)(x-(-5))$ for integer $a>1$."},{"title":"Expand to find $a+b$","content":"Expanding gives $f(x)=ax^2-a(8+(-5))x+a(8)(-5)$, so $b=-a(3)$ and $$a+b=a(1-(3))=-2a.$$"},{"title":"Pick a valid $a$","content":"With $a=2$ (integer $>1$), $a+b=-2\\cdot2=-4$. The answer is <strong>D</strong>."}]}